statements: SELECT * FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard ORDER BY supplier_id DESC
SELECT supplier_name, total_orders FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard WHERE total_orders > 100
SELECT supplier_name, average_delivery_time FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard WHERE supplier_rating > 4.5
SELECT supplier_name, total_orders, average_delivery_time FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard WHERE average_delivery_time < 2.5
SELECT * FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard ORDER BY supplier_rating
SELECT supplier_name, total_orders, average_delivery_time FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard WHERE supplier_rating > 4.5 ORDER BY total_orders DESC LIMIT 5
SELECT * FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard WHERE average_delivery_time < 2.5 ORDER BY supplier_rating ASC

SELECT supplier_id, supplier_name, SUM(total_orders) AS total_orders_sum FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard GROUP BY supplier_id, supplier_name HAVING total_orders_sum > 50 ORDER BY total_orders_sum DESC

SELECT supplier_name, supplier_rating, AVG(average_delivery_time) AS avg_delivery_time FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard GROUP BY supplier_name, supplier_rating HAVING avg_delivery_time < 3.5 ORDER BY supplier_rating DESC
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_suppliers, AVG(supplier_rating) AS avg_supplier_rating FROM SupplierPerformanceDashboard
SELECT supplier_name, supplier_rating FROM suppliers
SELECT * FROM orders
SELECT supplier_id, supplier_name, supplier_rating FROM suppliers ORDER BY supplier_name DESC
SELECT order_id, supplier_id, order_date FROM orders WHERE supplier_id = 1
SELECT supplier_id, supplier_name, supplier_rating FROM suppliers WHERE supplier_rating > 4
SELECT supplier_name, supplier_rating FROM suppliers WHERE supplier_rating > 4.5 ORDER BY supplier_rating DESC LIMIT 3;
SELECT supplier_name, COUNT(order_id) AS total_orders FROM suppliers LEFT JOIN orders ON suppliers.supplier_id = orders.supplier_id GROUP BY supplier_name HAVING COUNT(order_id) > 1;

SELECT supplier_name, MAX(order_total) AS highest_order_total FROM suppliers JOIN orders ON suppliers.supplier_id = orders.supplier_id GROUP BY supplier_name ORDER BY highest_order_total DESC LIMIT 1;
SELECT suppliers.supplier_name, orders.order_date FROM suppliers JOIN orders ON suppliers.supplier_id = orders.supplier_id WHERE orders.order_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';
SELECT supplier_name, AVG(supplier_rating) AS avg_rating FROM suppliers GROUP BY supplier_name HAVING AVG(supplier_rating) > 3.0 ORDER BY avg_rating DESC LIMIT 5;

SELECT s.supplier_name, r.rating_date, r.reliability_rating, r.quality_rating FROM suppliers s JOIN ratings r ON s.supplier_id = r.supplier_id WHERE s.supplier_location = 'New York' ORDER BY r.rating_date DESC LIMIT 5
